                    <description>&lt;p&gt; believe there is something wrong with fkmeans in trunk. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am using code from trunk (last checkout 6/30/11). To recreate is very simple:&lt;br/&gt;
1) change examples/bin/build-reuters.sh to use fkmeans and set -m 2&lt;br/&gt;
2) run build-reuters.sh&lt;br/&gt;
3) Dump the cluster. I&apos;m doing: ../../bin/mahout clusterdump -dt sequencefile -s ./mahout-work/reuters-kmeans/clusters-6 -b 100 -o ./reuters-clusterdump.txt  -d ./mahout-work/reuters-out-seqdir-sparse-kmeans/dictionary.file-0&lt;/p&gt;

